track_notes:
My route runs from Snowdon Ranger to the summit of Moel Cynghorion and then drops back down to the Snowdon Ranger path to head to Rhyd Ddu via the disused slate quarry at Glan-yr-afon. The missing section between Rhyd Ddu and Snowdon Ranger is pleasantly filled by a short trip on the Welsh Highland Railway.

Look for the turn to the left off the main track, marked for Llanberis. At the bwlch turn right just before the stile, following the fence to the summit.

From the summit continue towards Snowdon. Look for Llyn Ffynnon-y-gwas and aim to pass to its west, picking up the top of a track from the quarry. At the quarry continue until the permissive path crosses north-south - follow it through the quarry. After the quarry the land gets very boggy - be prepared!
track_title: Snowdon Ranger to Moel Cynghorion to Rhyd Ddu

track_notes: From Snowdon summit follow the hordes down the Llanberis path until a stone maker directs you left to cross the railway track (watch out for trains!). Easy path down to the bwlch. Turn right and start climbing. Its pretty unrelentingly steep. Prepare to be underwhelmed by the summit cairn.
track_title: From Snowdon via Snowdon Ranger path

track_notes: Rather than dodging the traffic take the forest track as if you were going to Mynydd Mawr, but turn right at the clearing and drop down to the camp site. Then a bit of road is unavoidable, as far as the turning to Bron-y-fedw-uchaf. Over the railway crossing head let and over the fields above Bron-y-fedw-isaf. Eventually you meet and cross the Snowdon Ranger path. Actually it might be better to jink right as I found the alternative path to Bwlch Maesgwm, a little further on, had been upgraded. My route was pretty indistinct. At the bwlch head right, up the summit.
